### Grand Total Estimate (Revised)

**Summary by Category:**
- Front stage platform: $520-556 (includes larger corner pockets)
- Front subwoofer system (with 3" recessed drivers & integrated AT covers): $1,821
- Rear subwoofer system (with 3" recessed drivers & integrated AT covers): $1,786
- Subwoofer electronics (PURIFI amps, DSP): $4,200-4,600
- Equipment rack (including access panel): $640-740
- Riser platform: $1,593-1,798
- Rear wall system: $315-425
- Crowson system: $1,800-2,600
- Main electronics: $8,650-10,700
- Speakers (including isolation): $8,270-10,870
- Screen/Projector: $32,000-34,000
- Acoustic treatment: $3,500-7,500
- Seating: $4,000-8,000
- **Total: ~$68,676-85,044**

**Rev 4.1 Cost Impact:**
- Front subs: +$145 (larger enclosures, integrated covers)
- Rear subs: +$330 (larger enclosures, integrated covers)
- Stage platform: +$13 (larger corner pockets)
- Eliminated: -$220 (separate stage front AT panels)
- **Net increase: +$268** (improved driver protection and professional appearance)

**Rev 5.0 Cost Impact:**
- Atmos speakers: +$880-1,180 (DIYSG Volt-10 vs. DIY Eminence build)
- Benefit: Guaranteed reference capability (107-108 dB) vs. marginal performance (104-105 dB)
- Result: Eliminates weak link in reference-level system, proper integration across all channels

**Notes:**
- Prices are estimates based on current market (2024-2025)
- Actual costs in 2027 may vary
- Does not include: Tools, consumables (paint, caulk beyond listed), HVAC modifications, electrical work, general room construction
- Professional calibration: $500-1,500 additional
- PURIFI amplification adds ~$2,200 over original NC502MP budget but provides critical silent operation and proper headroom
- Rev 4.1 adds 3" recessed driver mounting with integrated AT covers for +$268 net cost (improved protection and aesthetics)
- Rev 5.0 upgrades Atmos to DIYSG Volt-10 for +$880-1,180 (eliminates performance weak link, ensures reference capability)

